cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and NFAs.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for performing the translation of Parikh images.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of Parikh images of regular languages.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper presents an optimal algorithm for LTL model checking.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the complexity of membership for Parikh images, which is relevant to machine learning and natural language processing.
